  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I become a sub inspector in delhi police after graduation?",
  "response": "To become a Sub-Inspector (SI) in the Delhi Police after graduation, you need to follow a specific procedure which generally involves appearing for competitive exams and meeting certain eligibility criteria. Here's a step-by-step guide for you:\n\n1. **Eligibility Criteria**:\n   - **Educational Qualification**: You must have a Bachelor's degree from a recognized university.\n   - **Age Limit**: Typically, the age limit is between 20 to 25 years. Age relaxation is applicable for reserved categories as per government rules.\n\n2. **Examination**:\n   - The recruitment is usually conducted by the Staff Selection Commission (SSC) through the SSC CPO (Central Police Organization) exam.\n   - The examination consists of four stages:\n     - **Paper-I**: Written Examination (Objective Multiple Choice)\n     - **Physical Endurance Test (PET)**: Physical tests including running, long jump, high jump, etc.\n     - **Paper-II**: Written Examination (Objective Multiple Choice)\n     - **Medical Examination**: Basic health and fitness check.\n\n3. **Application Process**:\n   - Check for the SSC CPO exam notification on the official SSC website or other employment news sources.\n   - Register and fill out the online application form.\n   - Pay the application fee (if applicable).\n\n4. **Preparation**:\n   - **Written Exam**: Prepare for subjects including General Intelligence & Reasoning, General Knowledge & General Awareness, Quantitative Aptitude, and English Comprehension.\n   - **Physical Test**: Maintain physical fitness and practice running, jumping, etc.\n   - **Medical Exam**: Ensure you are in good health and meet the medical standards set by the authorities.\n\n5. **Admit Card and Exam**:\n   - Download your admit card from the SSC website when it's available.\n   - Appear for the exams on the scheduled dates.\n\n6. **Results and Further Process**:\n   - SSC will publish the results on their official website.\n   - Candidates who pass the written exams and physical tests will be called for document verification and medical examination.\n\n7. **Training**:\n   - Upon selection, candidates will undergo training at the designated police training academy.\n\n**Additional Tips**:\n- Stay updated with the latest notifications and exam dates.\n- Joining coaching classes for SSC CPO can be helpful.\n- Regular practice and revision are crucial for success in the written exams.\n- Physical fitness should be maintained and improved continuously.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to pursue a career as a Sub-Inspector in the Delhi Police after completing your graduation.",
